<span id="freeTextContainer16964009625569480667">This is a more satisfying conclusion to <i>The Once and Future King</i> which, for reasons I am a bit foggy on, was not included until a decade after White&apos;s death.<br/><br/>Philosophy, social studies, nature, violence...each takes it&apos;s turn beneath the microscope. Kindness and humanity are extolled. Nationalism is exposed for the evil it is. I can&apos;t say I could follow every train of thought, but that&apos;s probably a good thing as I have lots to look forward to in the many re-readings of this that I hope to have be</span>
  <span id="freeText16964009625569480667" style="display:none">This is a more satisfying conclusion to <i>The Once and Future King</i> which, for reasons I am a bit foggy on, was not included until a decade after White's death.<br /><br />Philosophy, social studies, nature, violence...each takes it's turn beneath the microscope. Kindness and humanity are extolled. Nationalism is exposed for the evil it is. I can't say I could follow every train of thought, but that's probably a good thing as I have lots to look forward to in the many re-readings of this that I hope to have before I croak.</span>
